  <description type="morphology">Plants less than 2.5 mm. Leaves broadly linear to lanceolate, 0.8–2.5 × 0.15–0.4
        mm; margins serrulate to strongly serrate distal to the proximal third; apex slenderly
        acuminate, papillose; costa not always apparent at the base, often filling the acumen,
        percurrent; areolation compact distally; median laminal cells smooth or slightly papillose;
        distal laminal cells somewhat papillose. Capsule with very few stomates, mostly near the
        base. Spores spherical or reniform, 43–107 × 35–75 µm, orange-brown.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Capsules mature year around.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Moist or drying disturbed soil;</description>
